**who —** The King of Eolis — the Elven King who explains the stopped fountain and the mutated Dwarves, and sends the swordsman into the World Tree to awaken the springs and destroy the Evil One

**what —** the Elven King who explains the stopped fountain and the mutated Dwarves, and sends the swordsman into the World Tree to awaken the springs and destroy the Evil One

**where —** FAX · Faxanadu — Hudson Soft, NES 1989 (Famicom 1987; Falcom's Xanadu line)  Framework inputs: Faxanadu; the World Tree; Eolis; the Mantras; the card-keys; Golds & Ranks  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)

**why —** He is the voice that names the task: the ruler of a ruined people who can only point at the tree and ask a stranger to climb it.

**how —** Crystallized from Faxanadu (NES 1989) — Famicom Xanadu, on Falcom's licensed Xanadu name.

**◌ the mythos —** He is the voice that names the task: the ruler of a ruined people who can only point at the tree and ask a stranger to climb it. a being of the World Tree and the climb to the Evil One

